						               													<description>A card game for family fishing fun.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Go ice fishing in Hokkaido and discover the best fishing spots, water depths, and bait options! Draw different event cards and see who can catch the most Wakasagi (Japanese pond smelt)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game, one &amp;quot;boss&amp;quot; player draws three fishing information cards without showing the other players. These other &amp;quot;fishermen&amp;quot; players, in turn, try to predict the fishing information by placing pieces of ice on the cards. Depending on how many of their predictions are correct, the boss will call out the sound &amp;quot;Kon!&amp;quot;. If the boss calls out more than two &amp;quot;Kon&amp;quot;s, it means a fish has been hooked. However, if the fisherman fails to call out &amp;quot;Hit!&amp;quot; before the boss finishes saying a total of 10 &amp;quot;Kon&amp;quot;s, the fish will get away!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the case that the fishermen calls out &amp;quot;Hit&amp;quot; in time, he or she will get to take a card from the Wakasagi fish pile. If not, the Boss will receive a card instead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After either player draws a fish card, he or she will also need to draw an event card. An event card can be either positive or negative (for example, get an extra 2 fish...or a fox steals one of your wakasagi cards). There's even an event card that forces a player to caw like a crow for his or her next turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
